ic accretion, which causes an\naccretion column and its base to occult the star, can explain most of the\nobserved light curves. Although compatible with the model, many of the stellar\ninclination angles are moderate and do not exclude mechanisms other than the\noccultation by an inner disk warp to account for dipper light curves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Jun 2021 18:11:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-14"}
