\npredetermined sizes, still under the monotone preference assumptions. For three\ngroups, this provides thus an algorithmic version of a recent theorem by\nSegal-Halevi and Suksompong (2021). A classical lemma from topology ensures\nthat every self-map of a simplex mapping each facet to itself is surjective.\nThis lemma has often been used in economics theory and our algorithm can be\ninterpreted as an FPTAS counterpart of its two-dimensional version.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Jun 2021 04:58:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 7 Jun 2021 01:31:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 22 Oct 2021 01:37:02 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 21 Dec 2022 00:56:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-22"}
