. Surprisingly, in-situ reflection high energy\nelectron diffraction (RHEED) indicates that some impurity phases always appear\nonce Sr ions are doped into NdNiO3 although the X-ray diffraction (XRD) data\nare of high quality. While these impurity phases do not seem to suppress the\nsuperconductivity, their impacts on the electronic and magnetic structure\ndeserve further studies. Our work demonstrates and highlights the significance\nof cation stoichiometry in superconducting nickelate family.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Jun 2021 13:46:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-20"}
